XPeng Motors is one of China’s leading smart electric vehicle (“EV”) companies. We design, develop, manufactures and market smart EVs that are seamlessly integrated with advanced Internet, AI and autonomous driving technologies. We are committed to in-house R&D and intelligent manufacturing to create a better mobility experience for our customers. We strive to transform smart electric vehicles... with technology and data, shaping the mobility experience of the future.

Job Description:

Due to the growth of our business, XSense.ai Inc. is in demand for professional services of a Senior Software Engineer. The Senior Software Engineer will be responsible for the following duties:
• Develop algorithms for localization and map fusion using a variety of sensors such as IMU, GNSS and multiple cameras;
• Train machine learning and deep learning models on a computing cluster to perform radar object detection;
• Design and implementation localization modules to estimate vehicle pose, orientation and speed based on a variety of sensors and multiple cameras, using scientific analysis and mathematical models to predict and measure outcome;
• Optimize deep neural networks and the associated preprocessing/postprocessing code to run efficiently on an embedded device;
• Modify existing software to correct errors, to adapt it to new hardware, or to upgrade interfaces and improve performance;
• Store, retrieve, and manipulate data for analysis of software system capabilities and requirements in order to improve the stability, safety, and security of onboard software;
• Work closely with systems integration and test teams on development and testing of algorithms on localization and map fusion;
• Lead, review, comment, and support junior software engineers of the company;
• Prepare progress reports and documentation of productivity with respect to implemented projects.

Minimum Requirements:
• Master’s degree in Computer Engineering, Electrical Engineering or related.
• Familiar with Linux and proficiency in C/C++, Python, and MATLAB.
• Experience with deep learning framework like TensorFlow and PyTorch.
• Solid knowledge and insight understanding of computer vision.
• Clear communication and ability to work with others.

Apply to XSense.ai Inc. 15070 Avenue of Science, suite 101, San Diego, CA 92128.

What do we provide:
• A fun, supportive and engaging environment
• Opportunities to pursue and work on cutting edge technologies
• Competitive salary
• Snacks, lunches and fun activities

We are an Equal Opportunity Employer. It is our policy to provide equal employment opportunities to all qualified persons without regard to race, age, color, sex, sexual orientation, religion, national origin, disability, veteran status or marital status or any other prescribed category set forth in federal or state regulations

